<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-D7BB618C-7039-484C-951B-5A82E225FBC4" version="4" lang="en-US"?><tsTroubleshooting xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-D7BB618C-7039-484C-951B-5A82E225FBC4" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.2" domains="(topic tsTroubleshooting)                            (topic hi-d)    (topic sdlVariables-c)                             (topic ut-d)                             (topic indexing-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c tsTroubleshooting oceTroubleshooting-c)   " class="- topic/topic tsTroubleshooting/tsTroubleshooting "><title translate="no" class="- topic/title ">1548 Lamp segment 5 is failing </title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-B87BF88B-91B2-4C27-A55C-91B9B6986C8A"><p class="- topic/p ">1548 Lamp segment 5 of the pre curing lamp is failing. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The current or voltage of this lamp segment is out of range, light output may be too low. 
</p><note class="- topic/note " id="GUID-B92025CF-2094-448B-9962-25D94A3B479C"><p class="- topic/p ">For R4.4.0.0 and higher: check for the following service warnings in PRISMAservice for additional information: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">1956 Curing LAMP1_FAULT active 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">1957 Curing LAMP2_FAULT active 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">1958 Curing fault message reported 
</p></note><note class="- topic/note " id="GUID-FC07EC81-ECBD-436E-A276-0428B755B004"><p class="- topic/p ">If this error only occurs during media calibration and not during a print job then replace the corresponding lamp. 
</p></note></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category></metadata></prolog><tsBody class="- topic/body tsTroubleshooting/tsBody "><tsSymptoms id="GUID-33E1B64A-E818-4500-A780-C8BC692D14B2" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsSymptoms "/><tsCauses id="GUID-8D3A5921-832C-4F25-A337-358C81AB97E1" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsCauses "><p class="- topic/p ">Electrical connections 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Verify the bundle between the <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Lamp control PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 01PBA03 </compcodenr></comp> and the <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Pre curing lamp PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 01PBA01 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">PRE_CURE_LAMP</compsignal></comp> (reported in the MRI of the error. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Verification can be done by swapping the bundles of both lamps (at controller and lamp side). Also check if the bundle is not damaged inside the IGUS chain. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If on next startup the segment failure is reported on the other lamp or if no segment failure occurs then the bundle is defect/unreliable. 
</p></tsCauses><tsDiagnose id="GUID-75AB2DE8-328A-4AED-9B40-628DAA7A2B6A" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsDiagnose "><p class="- topic/p ">Check / Reseat / Replace the bundle. 
